# Testing

## Unit tests (Vitest)

- Colocate tests as `*.test.ts` next to source (e.g. `src/lib/plan.test.ts`).
- Run: `npm test` or `npm run verify`.
- Prefer testing real behavior over mocking internals when cost is low.

## E2E (Playwright)

- Specs live in `e2e/` (e.g. `e2e/locations.spec.ts`).
- Helpers: `e2e/helpers/auth.ts`.
- Run: `npm run test:e2e` (needs `DATABASE_URL`, `AUTH_SECRET`).

## When adding features

- Add or extend unit tests for lib logic (validation, plan gating, availability, webhooks).
- Add e2e coverage for critical user flows when touching booking or dashboard paths.

Do not weaken tests to make CI pass — fix the underlying issue.
